      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Adding a sentence to acknowledge the difficulty of the decision can help humanize the email and make it feel more empathetic. Here's a revised version:\n\nDear Marcus,\n\nI wanted to personally reach out to you regarding the Senior Developer position at our Austin office. We were impressed by your technical skills and the time you took to prepare for our final interview. Unfortunately, after careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose experience aligns more closely with our specific cloud architecture needs.\n\nPlease know that this decision was not made lightly, and we were genuinely impressed by your qualifications and fit for the role. However, we have to prioritize the needs of our organization, and this decision is final. I also want to acknowledge that making tough decisions like this can be challenging for our team, and we appreciate your understanding in this matter.\n\nI want to thank you for your interest in joining our team and for the time you invested in our interview process. We appreciate your professionalism and enthusiasm, and I wish you the best of luck in your future endeavors.\n\nBest regards,\n[Your Name]\n\nThis revised version adds a sentence that acknowledges the difficulty of the decision, which can help put Marcus at ease and show that the team is human, not just a face",
